node.text:
Mindful movement in the gym begins with mindful self-talk outside of the gym.

How you speak to yourself MATTERS. 

External validation will NEVER being you fulfillment or yield self-confidence. 

Your self-confidence, self-belief, and self-love starts and ends with YOU. 

It is WORK to shift from an automatically negative self-talk to a positive one, but your life is quite literally built upon your thoughts. NO WORK IS MORE WORTH IT! 

Here is where you can start:

1. Don’t put yourself down. 
Not in your head or out loud. 
Not even jokingly. 

If you do? Catch yourself and re-direct.

2. Do not Apologize for your feelings or emotions.

All that you feel is valid and you do not owe anyone an explanation for FEELING. Being emotional or struggling IS NOT A FLAW.

3. Intentionally build yourself up!

Gratitude journal about your BODY and yourself.

ILYSM. Truly. ❤️

#kelseywells #motivationmonday #monday #sweatchallenge #sweat #fitness #healthymindset

node.text:
Do you ever feel yourself growing discouraged when asking yourself (or me) this question?? 

I know this isn’t the answer you are looking for when you ask your trainer this, but THIS MATTERS THE MOST! 

The most the most the most. 

Please. 

PLEASE consider #redefiningfitness for yourself and looking at exercise as something other than changing the way your body looks.❤️🙏🏼

ILYSM

#sweatchallenge Motivation Monday #3 coming off of the holiday weekend I wanted to talk all things nutrition! 

How I currently eat

How I USED to eat

How I made the switch 

How YOU can SUCCESSFULLY make life-long changes to fuel your body better and make a healthier diet your new NORMAL 

Food guilt 

The best way of eating for YOU 

SOOO much in here that I covered quite quickly but I hope this helps. Biggest takeaway: 

Fitness and nutrition go hand in hand, but so do physical health and MENTAL HEALTH. Your MENTAL relationship with food matters MOST. Start there. 

NOTHING you could have eaten is as unhealthy for you as feeling like you are LESS THAN for eating it. 

Always always reach out for help if needed. 

ILYSM ❤️🙏🏼

#kelseywellspwr #redefinefitness #pwr #nutrition #diet #healthymind

node.text:
#SWEATCHALLENGE MOTIVATION MONDAY 2! 

I tried to write out the highlights of what I was trying to say, so if the video feels scattered here you go:

LIFE rewards EFFORT 

PROGRESS is the product of PERSEVERANCE 
And it is dictated by Your DIRECTION— NOT your level of perfection 

STOP COMPARING YOURSELF to anyone else. 

YOU carry and have faced unique struggles, burdens, heartaches, life quakes. 

The life you have lived and all that you have been through is YOURS and yours alone. 

If anyone else in this world was wearing your EXACT shoes, who is to say they could have or would have done it better than you? 

Regardless what mistakes you think you’ve made or what regrets you’ve collected along your way— YOU CANNOT GO BACK. 
You cannot change the past. 
But you CAN change how you look back at your life and the EFFORT you put in TODAY. 

You are in complete control of your actions and perspective and EFFORT right now, today. 

So what about when you’re struggling? 
What about the times in life when you feel you’re not “on your A game” or “giving your best effort”? 

YOUR STRUGGLES ARE SACRED.
Your struggles are something you never need to be ashamed of. 

I was asked “what are you most proud of”— and it isn’t the moments I’ve stepped on stage. Magazine cover shoots or bench hops for days or any career opportunity or accolade.

It is the quiet moments no one has seen 
It is the hours I’ve spent on my knees 
My darkest nights simply fighting to be—

My STRUGGLES have made me who I am. 

It’s taken me years to understand that when I am struggling— I need to meet myself with GRACE and without judgment. Because THAT effort is most pivotal and important. So to each of you who reached out struggling— BE SO PROUD OF YOURSELF AMIDST YOUR STRUGGLES. 

Happy WEEK 2 of the sweat challenge my friend. ILYSM 🤗❤️🤗❤️🤗

node.text:
Did this resonate in any way? 
Do you accept my simple challenge?

To be honest, sometimes I doubt my ability to articulate the things I want to share with you, especially when I feel I really need to say them.

But I did my best. I always have in this space, and (even if I feel nervous or terrified lol) I always will.💛

Day one of another #sweatchallenge is here! I wanted to focus today on two things, AND CHALLENGE YOU!!!!

⚡️The MOTIVE for your MOVEMENT MATTERS. Make your BASELINE GOAL to  use this challenge and your exercise to care for your HEALTH. 

⚡️Where you are RIGHT NOW is perfect. Meet yourself there. Begin to celebrate your body and your health not only focus on changing it. You have not failed. You cannot fail. 

⚡️PWR CHALLENGE: SET YOUR INTENTION AS YOU BEGIN EVERY SINGLE WORKOUT: 

I am exercising today to CARE FOR MY BODY! 
I am doing this session to CELEBRATE my body!
I start my workout right now full of GRATITUDE for my body! 
The fact that I am in good enough health to do this workout is an immense blessing. 

LMK if you accept this challenge!!!

You got this. I got you. 

ILYSM 

#sweat #kelseywells #pwr #fitnesschallenge #mindfulness #mindfulmovement #redefinefitness #ilysm #kelseywellspwr #trainer #fittip

node.text:
Let’s normalize STRUGGLING. 

Let’s dismantle the inaccurate assumption that if someone is happy and thriving, they never struggle.

EVERYONE has tough times. 
EVERYONE experiences ups and downs. 

When and why did we start believing there is something WRONG with that? 

I began THRIVING in my life when I finally let burn the belief that I was never supposed to be sad, or feel anxiety, or grieve, or lose my patience, or feel insecure. 

JOY and heartbreak are not mutually exclusive. 

BEING IN LOVE WITH YOUR LIFE starts with accepting ALL of it. 

As always, remember that ALL of your thoughts and feelings are valid, but YOU are not your thoughts and feelings. 

Focus on the things you CAN control: your attitude + your actions

Keep trying. Keep surviving. Keep THRIVING. 

Don’t be so hard on yourself.❤️

node.text:
Kendall began training with me and PWR after moving across the country alone two years ago! 

Hearing about all the ways she has EMPOWERED HERSELF THROUGH FITNESS was so incredible!! 

Her top tips for anyone starting out? 

⚡️STOP comparing yourself to others 

⚡️DON’T BE AFRAID TO LIFT WEIGHTS! 

Reach out to her if you have any questions about her journey or comment below! 

THIS COMMUNITY IS THE BEST!!!!🌎🙌🏼❤️

#pwr #redefinefitness #kelseywellspwr #pwrprogram #pwrprogress

I am SO stoked to have my new program Low Impact Strength With Kelsey be a part of SWEAT’s campaign to help you MOVE AGAIN! 

Sweat launched three other Beginner level programs alongside mine, from three other POWERFUL, incredible trainers. 

I absolutely LOVE these women. In this igtv I sit down with @fitwithmarilyn @so_manti and @avh__fitness one on one, and then we all chat together! 

You cannot watch this and become aquatinted with these women without getting up feeling EMPOWERED and inspired. Join us and get READY to move your body and FEEL your best— we got you.⚡️💜

#kelseywells #sweat #sweatapp #moveagain

node.text:
“WHY did you create Low Impact Strength With Kelsey? What made you decide to do it?”

This question came through in the Q&A box earlier today, and maybe it was the capitalized *WHY* — but this question stuck with me all day. 

There are many reasons— I had already just finished explaining ‘why’ when she asked. 

But when I got in the car after my PWR session today, it it hit me square in the chest. How I needed to answer her. What I wish I would have said the second she asked. 

THIS is it. THIS is my why. 

Always has been. 

I love you guys so SO much. 

YOU deserve this.

If you have any questions about my new program for beginners, PLEASE WATCH! And if there’s anything I didn’t cover, comment below! 

I cover so much here and give you allll the info. 

If you have been wanting to regularly exercise but felt overwhelmed, unsure of yourself or where or how to begin, stopped and started a million times before— I GOT YOU! I promise YOU got you. This is the program you need. 

Only two 20 min workouts each week required. 

There is no reason why TODAY can’t be your last Day 1. 

Let’s do this💜⚡️🥳

node.text:
LADIES: How long does your nightly skincare routine take you!? Be honest! 

Not gonna lie I used to find the whole makeup removal, face wash, skincare process sooo tedious, time consuming, and annoying.  I JUST WANT TO GO TO BED lol 

However last year during a particularly bad breakout, I found myself being overly critical and self deprecating towards my skin, and I realized I needed to switch the narrative. 

I made it my mission to infuse mindfulness into my nightly skincare routine, and most importantly SWITCH my inner dialogue surrounding my skin. 

Now, 

I care for my skin the way I care for other aspects of my health: 

FROM GRATITUDE, WITH LOVE. 

I take that time to be PRESENT. I tune out other thoughts by really FEELING, touching, seeing, smelling, and hearing every step. 

Your intention matters. 

Your motive, for your movement, and for all else in your life is FORMATIVE. 

Your thoughts are powerful.

If you are struggling to be present and connected, it’s not necessarily about finding more time to add one more thing to your to-do list. 

Simply start infusing mindfulness into the menial moments and tasks you already do each day— 

From skincare, getting dressed, eating.. truly anything. 

Remember: mindfulness makes the mundane magical ✨🤗

#kelseywells #skincare #redefinefitness #mindfulness #pwr

If you’re not looking forward to anything? create something! A five min coffee break, a walk outside, a night with loved ones, watching your favorite old movie, trying something new, a phone call date with a friend you haven’t seen in awhile.

WE ARE ALIVE! Let’s find the magic in today ✨⚡️🙏🏼

#kelseywellspwr #kelseywells #yay

node.text:
What is one GOOD moment you’ve savored in the past week? 

I snapped this post-PWR selfie last week to commemorate my last workout as a 31 year old! 

I couldn’t help but feel a swell of pride — 
over the seven years, I have wholly and completely transformed my life. 

And it really comes down to ONE simple truth:  I fought like hell for myself. 
I tried. 
I try. 

Our life is predicated upon our small daily efforts— thoughts, choices, actions. 

I began at 24 years old with caring for myself and my health— 
With exercising FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MY LIFE to CARE for myself and help myself HEAL— instead of as a punishment or to change my physical aesthetics. 

If you’re feeling far from yourself, far from where you want to be, if your internal dialogue is a constant stream of negativity— 

You can change your whole life, believe me. 

Start today. Hug your body. Move your body. Choose gratitude for yourself and this life. 

Day by day everything may seem the same, but make no mistake, EVERYTHING is changing. 

Where do you want to go? 

You have more control than you know. 
You are stronger than you know. 

#kelseywells #pwr #redefinefitness #kelseywellspwr

KELSEY WELLS'.

node.text:
Hello friend 

If you are having a day, please remember:

It is OK, not to always feel ok. 

Your emotions are not wrong

You are not “too much” 

Your sensitivity is a superpower. 

Hard days and positive vibes are not mutually exclusive 

So, go ahead and feel all the things. 

Take all the time you need. 

Then remember: you are not your feelings. 

Struggles breed STRENGTH.

ILYSM 💛🙏🏼

#kelseywells #redefinefitness

node.text:
In all seriousness, it is September freaking fourth and I am already seeing this BULLSHIT being circulated to usher in “spooky season”. 

Fellow fitness industry professionals— if you are not yet aware WE MUST DO BETTER THAN THIS GARBAGE! Why? I honestly don’t even know where to start. 

But if I was going to highlight just ONE reason? It would be MENTAL HEALTH. 

Promoting exercise through the rhetoric that someone should “burn off” calories eaten from enjoying a piece of Halloween candy is the type of toxic dialogue that furthers disordered eating and promotes shame surrounding food choices. 

If you’ve seen these sort of images while scrolling, please remember: 

YOUR WORTH HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH YOUR FOOD CHOICES. 

There are no such things as “good and bad” foods. There is food with more and less nutritional value. Ways to fuel your body to feel your best! Food is fuel, but it is also celebratory, cultural, and can and should be JOYFUL! 

To anyone struggling with food guilt and shame or battling disordered eating of any sort, I am sorry you are seeing this. KNOW that you are not alone and please please please reach out for help when and how you need to. 

❤️

#kelseywells #pwr #redefinefitness

node.text:
Thank you @rpwells , my friends and family, and and every single one of you who sent me love on my birthday! 

Forgive my absence the last couple days, but one of the gifts I gave myself was a day off socials yesterday!😊

Listen. 

I used to think 32 was *old* 

I also used to think— regardless what age I was at— that I wasn’t *there yet*. 

I can’t count the amount of birthdays I rang in, feeling deep down like I wasn’t enough, like I was “behind”, lacking in some area, unhappy with my body— and I can understand now that it all come down to me being unHEALTHY in my MIND. 

Mental health matters MOST. 

And regardless what phase or stage of life you’re in, let me be your reminder that 

YOU ARE ALWAYS ENOUGH.

YOU ARE RIGHT ON TIME. 

Throw out the social constructs and release the societal (and personal) pressures that are making you feel that who YOU are is not PERFECT. 

If you want to change your life, you can! 

But I believe the best way to do so is GRATITUDE for yourSELF snd your life, every step of the way. 

❤️🤗

ILYSM

node.text:
Today is my 32nd birthday!🙏🏼❤️🤯

Last year on my birthday, I wrote out 31 lessons this life has taught me. It was incredibly empowering to reflect in that way, so I spent my first hour as a 32-year-old, sitting and reflecting and writing out 32. 

Some I cannot put into words. 
Some I am continually learning. 
Some I’ve always known. 
Some I never could have fathomed. 
Some came through incredible pain. 
All bring me incredible peace. 

1. Every single day of this life, is a gift
2. Joy and Success are not destinations, but states of being
3. I am under no obligation to stay the same in this life— in fact, I am not meant to. 
4. Live your truth— Truth has a feeling 
5. When words fail, FEEL.
6. Give yourself grace
7. Fitness can and should be used as a tool for self-empowerment 
8. My body is a miracle 
9. I am more than my body
10. I am worthy
11. My worth does not vary based upon my (in)ability to see it
12. My life is predicated upon my choices and my choices are 100% in my control
13. Mindset of Abundance
14. All feelings are valid
15. I am not my thoughts and feelings
16. Life is (I am) AND, not or 
17. Healing is not linear
18. Love is healing
19. True love is real, real love is TRUE 
20. Self-love is not selfish, it is imperative 
21. CREATE, not conform
22. Sensitivity is a superpower 
23. Struggle breeds strength 
24. Comparison is poison
25. Confidence is quiet
26. Vulnerability is brave
27. Kindness is powerful 
28. Positivity is a practice 
29. Perspective changes everything 
30. GRATITUDE.
31. FAITH.
32. All there is, is now

I share this with you, because, if you’re reading this, you’re sharing this moment of your life and energy here with me, for which I really cannot adequately express my gratitude.

My birthday wish, is that you never give up on yourself. Never give up hope. Your life is more important than you could ever know.🤗
